<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="promise-v">promise <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /'prɒmɪs/    美 /'prɑːmɪs/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>许诺；保证；答应：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— She’s not coming tonight. 
她今晚不来了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— But she promised. 
但她答应过的。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>promise to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The new monitor promised to do the best she could for us all.
新班长承诺会为我们大家竭尽全力。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>promise (sb) + (that) 从句:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I promise that you will get all your money back. 
我保证你会拿回你所有的钱。</p><footer>北师大⑧ – 23</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>promise sb sth / promise sth to sb:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She has been promised a new bike. 
有人答应给她买辆新自行车。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ve promised the book to Susan. 
我已经答应把这本书给苏珊了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>有...的希望；有...的可能：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Those clouds promise rain tomorrow. 
那些云预示着明天有可能下雨。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>promise to be sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It promises to be a fine day. 
天气有望好转。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>promising /'prɒmɪsɪŋ/ adj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a promising lawyer
有前途的律师</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The new movie promises <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (be) one of the biggest money-makers of all time.  （2010 辽宁改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. to be  </p></div>